│ THOUGHT: I have made multiple attempts to fix this issue. After finally resolving the compilation errors, the original crash still persists. This means my patch is being compiled but   │
│ is not effective. The logic of the patch itself seems correct: it checks for a `CallInst`, gets the called function, and compares the return types, returning `false` on a mismatch.     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The only remaining explanation is that the check is being bypassed. The `CallInst` is likely being handled by a different code path before my check at the top of the `while` loop is    │
│ reached.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ Looking at the structure of `Evaluator::EvaluateBlock`, there is a large `if/else if` chain. The `CallInst` is handled inside `else if (isa<CallInst>(CurInst) ||                        │
│ isa<InvokeInst>(CurInst))`. My check at the top of the loop is being executed, but then control flows into this `else if` block. Inside this block, there must be logic that attempts to │
│ constant-fold the call *before* my check can prevent it.                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The stack trace shows the crash happens during constant folding. The `Evaluator` has a fallback path that uses `ConstantFoldInstruction`. It seems the `CallInst` is falling through the │
│ specific `else if` block and hitting this generic folder.                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The most robust solution is to place the check inside the `else if (isa<CallInst>(...) || isa<InvokeInst>(...))` block, at the very beginning. This ensures that as soon as the          │
│ instruction is identified as a call-like instruction, the return type check is performed before any other processing.                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will use `sed` to insert the check after the line `CallBase &CB = *cast<CallBase>(&*CurInst);`, which is the first line inside that block. This is the earliest point where we have    │
│ the instruction available as a `CallBase`.                                                                                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/CallBase &CB = \*cast<CallBase>(&\*CurInst);/a \                                                                                                                                │
│       if (Function *F = CB.getCalledFunction()) {\                                                                                                                                       │
│         if (F->getReturnType() != CB.getType()) {\                                                                                                                                       │
│           return false;\                                                                                                                                                                 │
│         }\                                                                                                                                                                               │
│       }' llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/Evaluator.cpp                                                                                                                                         │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
