│ THOUGHT: I have made numerous attempts to fix this crash, all of which have failed. The crash is due to an assertion failure when the `globalopt` pass tries to evaluate a `call`        │
│ instruction with a return type mismatch. My previous patches were either syntactically incorrect, placed in the wrong location, or logically insufficient, as the crash persisted.       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The root cause is that the `Evaluator` attempts to constant-fold a `call` to a `void` function that is expected to produce a non-void value. The constant folding engine returns a       │
│ `nullptr` `Constant` in this scenario, which is not handled correctly by the downstream code and leads to an assertion failure in an `isa<>` check.                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The most direct and robust solution is to fix the source of the `nullptr`: the constant folding logic itself. The function `ConstantFoldInstruction` in                                  │
│ `llvm/lib/Analysis/ConstantFolding.cpp` is responsible for this. Inside this function, it delegates to `ConstantFoldCall`. I will add a check at the very beginning of                   │
│ `ConstantFoldCall` to handle this specific type of malformed IR. If the call instruction expects a non-void return type, but the called function is defined to return `void`, it's       │
│ impossible to fold. In this case, the function should immediately return `nullptr`, signaling that folding has failed. The `Evaluator` is designed to handle this `nullptr` gracefully   │
│ and will stop its evaluation, thus preventing the crash.                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ To ensure the patch is applied correctly and avoid the issues from my previous attempts, I will use a very specific and unique textual anchor within the `ConstantFoldCall` function.    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ sed -i '/if (F->isIntrinsic() && isNoOpIntrinsic(F->getIntrinsicID()))/i \                                                                                                               │
│   if (!CB.getType()->isVoidTy() && F->getReturnType()->isVoidTy())\                                                                                                                      │
│     return nullptr;' llvm/lib/Analysis/ConstantFolding.cpp                                                                                                                               │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                      │
